cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper studies three classical NP-hard combinatorial optimization problems on deterministic scale-free networks, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies scale-free networks, which are commonly found in social and information networks. The algorithms designed in the paper are also applicable to such networks. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses the properties of random graph models, which are commonly used in neural and evolutionary computing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a greedy algorithm for combinatorial optimization problems on deterministic scale-free networks, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper studies combinatorial optimization problems, which are commonly studied in game theory. The results on the approximability of these problems may be of interest to researchers in this field.
